        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 3:48PM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 348 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Belvidere, or 20 miles northwest of Fairbury, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Alexandria around 400 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
